    "recap_headline": "Rice University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Houston-\nKutter-Gage Webb\nand\nMason Ashlock\neach drove in two runs, and three Rice relievers combined to throw six shutout innings as Rice downed UTRGV 7-3 at Reckling Park on Tuesday Night.\nHow it Happened:\nThe Vaqueros jumped out to a 2-0 lead in the top of the first, but Rice carried over its offensive momentum from the weekend in Arizona and had an immediate answer in the bottom of the first.\nHiram Bocachica Jr.\n,\nColin Robson\n, and\nJC Davis\nopened the game with singles, with Davis bringing home Bocachica. Davis came home two outs later on a single by\nKutter-Gage Webb\n, and\nMason Ashlock\nsingled home the third run, scoring\nGaret Boehm\n.\u00a0 UTRGV struck back to tie the game with a run in the top of the third, but once again, Rice had an immediate answer in its half of the inning. Davis beat out an infield single to lead off the inning, and\nPaul Smith\nfollowed with a bloop double down the left field line to put runners at second and third. Webb singled to center to score Davis, and Ashlock followed with a sacrifice fly. The Vaqueros put two runners on with one out in the fourth, but the combination of\nBrayden Sharp\n,\nEthan Atchley\n, and\nCarson Kuhn\ncombined to retire the next 15 in a row while the offense added two runs in the bottom of the fourth to build some breathing room. Kuhn gave up a one-out single in the ninth to snap the streak, but closed out the game with a double play.\nNext Up:\nRice returns to the road next weekend to open American Conference play at South Florida this weekend.\u00a0 The series opens at 5:35 on Friday, followed by a 1:05 pm game on Saturday, and wraps up at 12:05 on Sunday.\nNotes\nThe Owls improved to 13-9 on the season, 7-3 at home, and 30-30-1 vs. UTRGV.\nRice has won 10 of its last 13 games overall and four straight at home.\nThe Owls are four games over .500 for the second time this season. Prior to 2026, the last time there were as many as four games over .500 was the end of the 2016 season, when they finished 38-24.\nThey reached 13 wins in their 22\nnd\ngame, the fewest games since they opened 2016 with an identical 13-9 record.\nSmith and\nCole Green\ndoubled in the game to give Rice 19 doubles in the last five games.\nWebb extended his hitting streak to five games and is hitting .688 (11x16) with 10 RBI over that stretch.\nGreen's double extended his on-base streak to 12 games while Robson extended his streak to 11 games."
  },
